<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1902-12-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1902-12-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="576" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d576">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Meyer</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-12-18"><hi rend="italic">December 18,
                                    1902</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Hay states that the United States minister to Venezuela telegraphs
                            that the Government of Venezuela confers upon him full powers to enter
                            into negotiations on the part of Venezuela to settle the present
                            difficulties with Italy, Germany, and Great Britain.</p>
                        <p>Mr. Meyer will communicate the Venezuelan proposition to the Government
                            of Italy and ascertain if it is disposed to assent thereto.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>